The South African Social Security Agency (SASSA) has suspended home, clinic, and hospital visits and encouraged their beneficiaries to avoid collecting their grants on the first day of payment. This, after President Ramaphosa’s declaration of a National State of Disaster and the prohibition of large gatherings of no more than 100 people. SASSA spokesperson, Paseka Letsatsi said: ” We work with people and communities. This situation calls for urgent action to be taken, looking at our daily and monthly business as SASSA and South African Post Office (SAPO).” Precautionary measures in all SASSA offices with immediate effect, to ensure the safety of clients and staff and that no service interruption occurs, are as follows: <br />
